    <p class="price-note">Sub-Zero parts cost 30-50% more than U-Line or Viking equivalents — the build justifies it across a 15-20 year service life. Compressor replacement on a 12-year RO-2450 runs $1,800-$2,500, but a new RO-2450 retails $5,500+. Repair-vs-replace math typically favors repair through year 15 unless there are multiple compounding failures.</p>
